  "prompt": "What percentage of freshers are accepted into the IIM's every year?",
  "response": "The Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) are among the most prestigious business schools in India, and their admissions process is highly competitive. The acceptance rate for freshers (candidates with little to no work experience) varies across the different IIMs and depends on several factors such as the number of applicants, the criteria for selection, and the total number of seats available.\n\nOn average, the acceptance rate for the flagship Post Graduate Program in Management (PGP) at the older IIMs (like IIM Ahmedabad, IIM Bangalore, and IIM Calcutta) can be as low as 0.5% to 1%. For the newer IIMs, the acceptance rate might be slightly higher, but it is still significantly competitive.\n\nCandidates are selected based on their CAT (Common Admission Test) scores, academic performance, work experience (if any), performance in the Written Ability Test (WAT), Group Discussion (GD), and Personal Interview (PI).\n\nTo give a rough estimate, if we consider the total number of applicants to the CAT exam (which is usually in the range of 2 lakh to 2.5 lakh candidates), and the total number of seats across all IIMs (approximately 4000 to 5000 seats), the overall acceptance rate could be around 2% to 2.5%.\n\nHowever, it's important to note that the acceptance rate for freshers specifically might differ slightly because a significant portion of the admitted candidates often have some work experience. For freshers, the acceptance rate could be slightly lower due to the emphasis on work experience in the selection criteria.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to refer to the official IIM websites or their annual admission reports.",
